Rating: 4
This is a really versatile recipe. I have made it several times, and love to vary the type of beans and fish. I love beans, so rarely used canned. I soak my favorite overnight, and then simmer for 2-3 hours before adding to this recipe. I have used cannellini and scarlet runner, and both have been excellent. It's also easy to use whatever firm white fish is fresh at the market. May favorite so far are halibut and grouper. I agree with the previous reviewers, rendering the bacon first helps with keeping it crisp. If you have pancetta, it's even better than the bacon!

Rating: 4
